{
  "texts": [
    "S1c, S2c and Fig. 2c.",
    "When testing using input complex fields synthesized from the QuickDraw images, these PSNR values revealed (14.42 ± 0.94, 13.34 ± 1.10), (14.17 ± 1.01, 13.54 ± 1.61) and (14.72 ± 0.97, 13.46 ± 1.13), with exemplary diffractive output images visualized in Supplementary Figs.",
    "S1d, S2d and Fig. 2d, respectively.",
    "Once again, these PSNR values, along with the visualization results of the output patterns, demonstrate that all our diffractive models (following designs I, II and III) achieved successful reconstructions of the amplitude and phase channel information of the input complex fields, wherein the design III model presented slightly improved performance over the other two designs.",
    "Importantly, these analyses demonstrate the external generalization capabilities of our diffractive imagers, positioning them as general-purpose complex field imagers that can handle input complex field distributions markedly distinct from those encountered during their training stage."
  ]
}